  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\n>As a user\r\n>When I receive a contact request\r\n>I want to see an in-app notification\r\n>So that I can action it quickly\r\n\r\n### Requirements\r\n\r\nAccording to specs in [Figma - Shell for Mobile](https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=4537%3A515620&t=K8LzjFXgNxSmkffX-0), the new Activity Center will use different rules for notifications. In the old Notification Center, a 1:1 message immediately generates a notification.\r\n\r\n**Confirm the following behavior with Design team, because it might be outdated.** Some requirements will probably require changes in status-go.\r\n\r\n- Notification event happens if the user hasnâ€™t been 1on1 messaged by the other use in the previous 1 hour\r\n- Do not show if the user has been previously 1on1 messaged by the other user in the previous 1 hour\r\n- Do not show if muted\r\n- Do not show if user in 1-1 chat with this user\r\n",
